    "excerpt": "The four freedoms as articulated by President Franklin D. Roosevelt in his address before the 77th Congress of the United States. . . .",
    "content": "<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><a href=\"/translate/\" target=\"_blank\">Contribute&nbsp;a&nbsp;translation</a></th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Source (English)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n&#8230;In the future days,<br />\nwhich we seek to make secure,<br />\nwe look forward to a world<br />\nfounded upon four essential human freedoms.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThe first is freedom of speech and expression &#8211;<br />\neverywhere in the world.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThe second is freedom of every person<br />\nto worship <span class=\"divine-referent\">God</span> in his own way &#8211;<br />\neverywhere in the world.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThe third is freedom from want &#8211;<br />\nwhich, translated into world terms,<br />\nmeans economic understandings<br />\nwhich will secure to every nation<br />\na healthy peacetime life for its inhabitants &#8211;<br />\neverywhere in the world.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThe fourth is freedom from fear &#8211;<br />\nwhich, translated into world terms,<br />\nmeans a world-wide reduction of armaments<br />\nto such a point and in such a thorough fashion<br />\nthat no nation will be in a position<br />\nto commit an act of physical aggression<br />\nagainst any neighbor &#8211; anywhere in the world.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThat is no vision of a distant millennium.<br />\nIt is a definite basis for a kind of world<br />\nattainable in our own time and generation.<br />\nThat kind of world is the very antithesis<br />\nof the so-called new order of tyranny<br />\nwhich the dictators seek to create<br />\nwith the crash of a bomb&#8230;.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<p>The four freedoms as articulated by President Franklin D. Roosevelt in his address before the 77th Congress of the United States. The speech is recorded in the <em><a href=\"https://www.congress.gov/77/crecb/1941/01/06/GPO-CRECB-1941-pt1-2-2.pdf\">Congressional Record</a></em>, vol. 87, Part 1 (January 6, 1941) — Bound Edition, 77th Congress &#8211; 1st Session, pp. 44-47. The Four Freedoms were included in the unpublished 1966 edition of the CCAR Union Anthology, pages 229-230.</p>\n<h3>Source(s)</h3>\n<p><span style=\"float: right;\"><div id=\"attachment_62739\" style=\"width: 260px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/congressional-record-four-freedoms-speech-franklin-d--roosevelt-6-january-1941-page-1.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-62739\" src=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/congressional-record-four-freedoms-speech-franklin-d--roosevelt-6-january-1941-page-1-250x250.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-62739\" /></a><p id=\"caption-attachment-62739\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Congressional Record &#8211; Four Freedoms speech (Franklin D. Roosevelt, 6 January 1941), p. 44</p></div></span> <span style=\"float: left;\"><div id=\"attachment_62740\" style=\"width: 260px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/congressional-record-four-freedoms-speech-franklin-d--roosevelt-6-january-1941-page-2.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-62740\" src=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/congressional-record-four-freedoms-speech-franklin-d--roosevelt-6-january-1941-page-2-250x250.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-62740\" /></a><p id=\"caption-attachment-62740\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Congressional Record &#8211; Four Freedoms speech (Franklin D. Roosevelt, 6 January 1941), p. 45</p></div></span> <span style=\"float: left;\"><div id=\"attachment_62741\" style=\"width: 260px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/congressional-record-four-freedoms-speech-franklin-d--roosevelt-6-january-1941-page-3.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-62741\" src=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/congressional-record-four-freedoms-speech-franklin-d--roosevelt-6-january-1941-page-3-250x250.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-62741\" /></a><p id=\"caption-attachment-62741\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Congressional Record &#8211; Four Freedoms speech (Franklin D. Roosevelt, 6 January 1941), p. 46</p></div></span> <span style=\"float: left;\"><div id=\"attachment_62742\" style=\"width: 260px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/congressional-record-four-freedoms-speech-franklin-d--roosevelt-6-january-1941-page-4.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-62742\" src=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/congressional-record-four-freedoms-speech-franklin-d--roosevelt-6-january-1941-page-4-250x250.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-62742\" /></a><p id=\"caption-attachment-62742\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Congressional Record &#8211; Four Freedoms speech (Franklin D. Roosevelt, 6 January 1941), p. 47</p></div></span><span class=\"\" style=\"display:block;clear:both;height: 0px;margin-top: ;border-top-width:0px;border-bottom-width:0px;\"></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"float: right;\"><div id=\"attachment_62745\" style=\"width: 260px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/229.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-62745\" src=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/229-250x250.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-62745\" /></a><p id=\"caption-attachment-62745\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Union Anthology (CCAR 1966, unpublished) &#8211; p. 229</p></div></span> <span style=\"float: left;\"><div id=\"attachment_62746\" style=\"width: 260px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/230.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-62746\" src=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/230-250x250.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-62746\" /></a><p id=\"caption-attachment-62746\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Union Anthology (CCAR 1966, unpublished) &#8211; p. 230</p></div></span><span class=\"\" style=\"display:block;clear:both;height: 0px;margin-top: ;border-top-width:0px;border-bottom-width:0px;\"></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n",
